  "prompt": "How and when did Dhoni start his career?",
  "response": "Mahendra Singh Dhoni, commonly known as MS Dhoni, began his cricket career in the early 2000s. He made his debut in domestic cricket while playing for Bihar in the 1999-2000 season. Dhoni's performances in domestic cricket earned him a place in the India A team, where his impressive play caught the attention of the national selectors.\n\nDhoni's international debut came on December 23, 2004, in an ODI match against Bangladesh. Though he didn't have a successful start, he quickly established himself as one of India's key players. His breakout performance came during an ODI series against Pakistan in 2005, where he scored his maiden century. Dhoni's consistent performances eventually led to his inclusion in the Test and T20I teams, and he soon became one of the most successful and influential cricketers in Indian history.\n\nHis leadership skills were recognized when he was made the captain of the Indian T20 team for the inaugural ICC World Twenty20 in 2007, which India won under his captaincy. He eventually became the captain of the Indian ODI and Test teams, leading India to victories in various major tournaments, including the ICC Cricket World Cup in 2011 and the ICC Champions Trophy in 2013.",
